{
  "doc_id": "22513",
  "text": "The fluorescence sensor can convert the recognition between the molecular recognition unit and target into a fluorescence response signal and detect the concentration of the target by monitoring the fluorescence intensity. An MIFs was constructed by introducing fluorescent materials into the MIPs synthesis system. Figure 2 presents the preparation process of MIFs based on embedding fluorescent materials into MIPs [CITATION_1] . MIFs are highly selective, highly sensitive, specific, and stable compared to conventional sensors [CITATION_2] , and have been widely used to detect many kinds of pollutants [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] [CITATION_7] . Reprinted with permission from [CITATION_8] , copyright (2017) American Chemical Society.",
